{
  "text": "Setting up barriers to prevent wildlife contact with domestic livestock, or vice versa, is rather infrequent, and its use is limited to certain risk situations. For example, it may make sense to avoid badgers on cattle farms in TB endemic areas [CITATION_1] or to prevent wild boar contact with open air bred pigs or other livestock [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
